TY  - JOUR
AU  - Christoffersen, Peter
AU  - Jacobs, Kris
AU  - Pan, Xuhui (Nick)
T1  - The State Price Density Implied by Crude Oil Futures and Option Prices
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab011
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 2
SP  - 1064
EP  - 1103
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Both large oil price increases and decreases are associated with deteriorating economic conditions. The projection of the state price density (SPD) onto oil returns estimated from oil futures and option prices displays a U-shaped pattern. Because investors assign high state prices to large negative and large positive oil returns, the U-shaped SPD may steepen in either tail when economic conditions deteriorate. The positive return region of the SPD is more closely related to economic conditions. The oil SPD contains information about economic conditions and future security returns that is distinct from the information in the stock index SPD.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab011
ER  - 



